Question: How to read a file in Java?:
Answer:<<<api>>>: BufferedReader.readLine
<<<code>>>: BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
br.close();
<<<explanation>>>: The readLine() method of the BufferedReader class reads a line of text from the file. It returns null if the end of the file is reached.
